President Muhammadu Buhari has congratulated the president of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan, on the occasion of his 64th birthday, Jan. 12, 2023. The president, on Wednesday via a statement issued by his Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina, said Lawan has a profile of being one of the most experienced legislators in the country, having served eight years in the House of Representatives, 1999-2007, and almost 12 years in the Senate. Buhari said Lawan, after leaving his career path as a lecturer and researcher, deployed his knowledge in shaping policies and strengthening democracy in Nigeria by always showing maturity, and advocating a win-win for all stakeholders. READ ALSO: Kukah, Buhari All Smiles As They Meet In Aso Villa He further saluted what he called the “historic interventions” of the Senate President, particularly providing a peaceful and harmonious leadership for the 9th National Assembly that had translated into many gains for the country on legislation and passing of bills into law. Nonetheless, President Buhari prayed for the well-being of Senator Lawan and his family.